Cal Grant wrote:

> Actually, if you apply (hand-sprayer bottle) some POR Metal Ready or
> equivalent phosphoric acid dilution to the bare steel, it will keep and
> not rust pretty much forever. Rinse off before continuing body prep work
> when ready.

POR Metal Ready is good stuff, but it is pricey!  Save yourself some $$
and go to the Orange box and pick up some phosphoric acid (same stuff). 
I think the last time I bought some it was about 3 or 4 dollars for a
quart.  Significantly cheaper than the POR equivalent.

Steve
